title: Rolle Town Retreat
description: Rolle Town Retreat is a cozy waterfront escape located directly across from Man O’ War Cay and the famous Rolle Town sandbars. A small, secluded beach just steps from the cottage is perfect for watching the sunrise, swimming, or launching a kayak for a day on the water. The retreat offers a peaceful, private atmosphere while still being close enough to explore George Town and nearby attractions. With its calm setting, turquoise views, and easy access to Exuma’s natural beauty, Rolle Town Retreat is an ideal choice for couples or small families looking to unwind in paradise.

title: Bayview Villa 1
description: Bayview Villas sit directly on the water with a shared private beach and boat ramp, perfect for launching into the turquoise Exuma seas. Guests can request boat rentals directly through the property or arrange for car rentals to explore the island with ease. Located across from Man O’ War Cay and the Rolle Town sandbars, the villas enjoy some of the most breathtaking sunrise views in Exuma. The shared patio includes a covered lounge and dining space where you can relax and take in the view. Bayview Villas are an excellent choice for families, couples, or groups seeking comfort, convenience, and a true oceanfront escape.

title: Bayview Villa 2
description: Bayview Villas sit directly on the water with a shared private beach and boat ramp, perfect for launching into the turquoise Exuma seas. Guests can request boat rentals directly through the property or arrange for car rentals to explore the island with ease. Located across from Man O’ War Cay and the Rolle Town sandbars, the villas enjoy some of the most breathtaking sunrise views in Exuma. The shared patio includes a covered lounge and dining space where you can relax and take in the view. Bayview Villas are an excellent choice for families, couples, or groups seeking comfort, convenience, and a true oceanfront escape.

title: Ole Ike Bay
description: Ole Ike Bay is a luxurious oceanfront estate in Moriah Harbour National Park (Rolletown), built for travelers who want privacy plus high-end, “everything’s handled” comfort. Expect panoramic ocean views, a private beach and dock, and a private pickleball court for post-sandbar bragging rights. Inside, the home is stocked for real-life living: a chef-style kitchen, smart-home features, Sonos audio, and fast Wi-Fi/Starlink that actually works when you’re trying to “work from paradise.” With 3 bedrooms, 4+ bathrooms, and sleep space for up to 7, it’s ideal for families or a small group who want room to spread out. The cherry on top: daily butler/housekeeping service, so your biggest chore is deciding sunrise coffee or sunset cocktails.

title: Ocean View Villa
description: Ocean View Villa is a peaceful one-bedroom hideaway in Rolle Town, perfect for couples or a simple “pause button” getaway. It’s the kind of place where mornings are quiet, the views are the main character, and your day plan can be as ambitious (sandbars, beach hopping, boat day) or as lazy (coffee, book, repeat) as you want. A great base for exploring the Rolle Town sandbars area while keeping the vibe calm and uncrowded.

title: Seabiscuit
description: Seaside Cottage “Seabiscuit” is a laid-back waterfront home overlooking Exuma’s famous bonefish flats, with ocean views that make morning coffee on the balcony feel like a vacation ritual. Inside, you’ve got the easy comforts that matter, including a full kitchen, A/C, washer, BBQ grill, and on-site parking, plus it’s pet-friendly for travelers bringing a furry first mate. It’s a great pick for families, anglers, or anyone who wants a quiet home base that’s still within a short drive of George Town and popular beaches like Palm Bay and Jolly Hall.

title: Bonefish Bungalow
description: Bonefish Bungalow is a waterfront escape in Georgetown that’s tailor-made for anglers and laid-back island days. This entire apartment pairs breezy outdoor living (deck/patio) with the essentials inside, including A/C, laundry access, and a handy kitchenette for easy meals between beach time and fishing runs. You’ll also have access to an outdoor pool and on-site parking, plus you’re a short drive from favorites like Palm Bay Beach and Jolly Hall Beach, making it a comfortable home base for exploring Exuma.

title: Coral Breeze
description: Coral Breeze is a bright, breezy villa-style getaway in the George Town area that’s built for slow mornings and salty-air evenings. You’ve got a full kitchen for island breakfasts, A/C for those warm Exuma afternoons, and a private balcony/patio where the views do the heavy lifting, coffee at sunrise, cocktails at sunset. There’s also a washer (huge for beach days) and on-site parking, so day trips around the island are easy.

title: Cottage Cut Villas
description: Cottage Cut Villas is a relaxed beachfront villa hideaway in the George Town area, set on a private beach so you can swap schedules for sea breeze. It’s an “entire home” style stay with the comforts that matter when you’re actually living island life, not just visiting it: a full kitchen, laundry, A/C, plus a BBQ grill and outdoor furniture for easy dinners and sunset hangs.

title: George Town Retreat
description: Exuma Home Rentals is a comfortable entire apartment in George Town with a private pool, full kitchen, and the everyday essentials that make island life easy: A/C, free Wi-Fi, and an in-unit washer. It’s a great “home base” for exploring Exuma, with popular beaches like Palm Bay Beach and Jolly Hall Beach just a short drive away. After a beach day, come back, rinse off, and unwind poolside before heading out for dinner in town.

title: Anchor Villa
description: Tucked in Hooper’s Bay, Anchor Villa is a cozy cottage stay that puts you close to the good stuff: it’s just a short walk to Hooper’s Bay Beach, and a quick drive into George Town when you want groceries, restaurants, and marina vibes. Inside, you’ve got the essentials for an easy “island-living but still comfortable” trip, including A/C and internet access, plus a private kitchen so breakfast doesn’t require shoes. It’s a great base for beach days, boat days, and bike rides around the area (the beach is sometimes nicknamed “Turtle Beach”, but consider turtles a bonus sighting, not a guarantee).

title: Dreammaker
description: A true toes-in-the-sand Exuma escape on Moriah Harbour in Hartswell, this beachfront villa pairs postcard views with the convenience of your own boat dock/mooring. Start mornings with coffee to the sound of waves, grill fresh catch for sunset dinners, and enjoy all the comforts between beach sessions, including A/C, a full kitchen, and in-home laundry. You’re perfectly positioned for exploring the south, with Rolletown Tombs, Tropic of Cancer Beach, and Little Exuma beaches just a short drive away.

title: Over Water Bungalow
description: Overwater bungalow in Masters Harbor with its own beach and views of Redshank Cays. 1BR/1BA with A/C, Wi-Fi, kitchenette, and shared laundry. Enjoy a private deck with direct ladder access into the sea. Set on a property with multiple homes, close to Brown’s Marina and Blu on the Water—10 min to George Town, 20 min to the airport.

title: The Mandrin House
description: Luxury meets laid-back island living at this waterfront home in Hartswell, perfectly positioned with postcard views across the shimmering waters toward Moriah Cay. Start your mornings with coffee on the deck as the sea turns from glass to turquoise, then spend the day exploring Exuma the way it’s meant to be done: beach hopping, sandbar cruising, snorkeling, and sunset watching from your own slice of shoreline. Inside, you’ll find a polished, upscale space designed for comfort after long days in the sun, with everything you need to settle in, slow down, and live on “island time.” Peaceful, private, and perfectly placed for adventure, this home is an ideal base for couples, families, or friends looking for a true Exuma escape with a luxury edge.

title: J&L Beachfront Bliss
description: Bright, breezy 2-bedroom beachfront suite in Rolleville with direct beach access just steps away and gorgeous ocean views from your private patio. Includes a fully equipped kitchen, fast Wi-Fi, A/C, smart TV, beach gear (chairs, towels, cooler, umbrella), and free on-site parking. Quiet, peaceful location near Da Cabana Bar & Grill, and convenient to local eats, shops, and popular boat tours. Private entrance and fully private unit; beach path may be shared with guests on the other side of the duplex.

title: Saint Francis Resort & Marina
description: Saint Francis Resort & Marina is a laid-back, beachfront hideaway on Stocking Island, just across the water from George Town. It’s the kind of place you book when you want quiet mornings, salty air, and the feeling that the island is running on its own gentle clock. Guests have direct beach access, an on-site pool, and a waterfront restaurant and bar for easy island meals without hopping back and forth. Boaters love it too, thanks to the marina/dock setup, and it’s a great base for exploring Elizabeth Harbour, Chat ‘N’ Chill, sandbars, and all the classic Exuma boat-day magic. If you’re looking for a relaxed, ‘toes-in-the-sand’ stay that still keeps you close to town, this one checks a lot of boxes.

title: SerenityBlu - Your Dream Come True!
description: SerenityBlu is a bright, modern ocean-view escape in Rolle Town that’s built for true “Exuma exhale” mode. With 2 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, and 4 beds (plus space to sleep up to 6), it’s a great fit for couples, families, or a small crew who want comfort without losing that island vibe. The highlight is the private outdoor hot tub, perfect for sunset soaks after a boat day. Inside, you’ll find A/C, fast Wi-Fi, and an easy, open layout designed for relaxing between beach runs, sandbar adventures, and meals at nearby local spots. Quiet location, big views, and close enough to the action when you want it.

title: Luxury Meets Tranquility – Master Suite Villa at Calm Water Villas, Exuma
description: A beachfront master suite villa at Calm Water Villas in Bahama Sound, Exuma, built for quiet, toes-in-the-sand relaxation. Enjoy your own private pool, a breezy terrace/patio, air conditioning, a washer, BBQ grill, and convenient on-site parking. You’re also a short drive from Rolletown Tombs, Palm Bay Beach, Jolly Hall Beach, and Exuma International Airport (GGT)—making it a peaceful home base with easy access to the best of Great Exuma.
